cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CR

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and qualitative analysis to analyze social media data related to gang violence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves collaboration between social work researchers and data scientists, indicating a potential fit for cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with violence prevention and interruption, which could fit under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
